Location: Central Singapore
Salary: SGD 3800 - 5300 per month
Working Hours: Monday to Friday 830am – 530pm, Saturday 830am – 1230pm
Job Responsibilities:
· Out-patient
· Ensure smooth running &amp; maintenance of out-patient clinic
· Provide patient education &amp; counselling
· Maintain consumables &amp; medication stocks
· Assist the Medical Director in the consultation room and procedures both in &amp; outside the Centre
· Surgery
· Maintain stocks &amp; inventory of surgical consumables
· Assist in laser refractive procedures (LASIK, PRK &amp; Relex SMILE, etc) &amp; other minor
procedures
· Upkeep of operating theatre and instrument sterility
· Administrative Duties
· Coordinate with external parties (ie labs, hospitals, clinics &amp; operation theatre, etc) in the management of patients
· Coordinate with external vendors for purchasing and maintenance of equipment and services
· Organise the surgical listing of patients
· Assist the medical director on all administrative duties relating to the smooth running of the centre
Job Requirements:
· Fully registered with Singapore Nursing Board
· Candidate must possess at least Diploma/Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma in Nursing or equivalent
· At least 2Year(s) of working experience in a related field is required for this position
